data.text: The foothill GTV6 ?.. The car has been so abandoned, back in the 90's the GTV6 was so deprecated in value, the Milano and the GTV 6 were sold on avg  of around 1k or less. Shankle automotive in Nortridge went out of business in the late 80's,  Brad Bunch of Alfa Ricambi decided to drop the sales of Alfa parts in favor of Honda which was so booming. International Auto parts became a major player in selling Fiat, Alfa, Lancia parts.  Kenny Hudson my good friend, stop his involvement with Alfa due to lack of Alfa enthusiast .  Bill Werner of Alfa only shut down his garage in Glendale in the mid 90's, Ed Biolato of Alfa D, Italian closed his garage due to the lost he's chief mechanic Jose. Win of Ferrari and Alfa on San fernando Blvd shutdown his garage.  Several parts are no longer manufacture only NOS for which some of the parts are worn with age, the most vital part for the 116 body Alfa is donut joint which only last a few month if the car was brutally driven but because donuts (3 of them) were NOS which mean some of them were kept in stock for as old as 20 years or older!!! And these are over 1000$ installed for 3 of them, Now you understand why Alfa is what it is today!!
Most of the above mentioned people are my friend some of them still alive, some are too old many were deceased..
